[Weekly Briefing] Suzuka - West - 2019s3 Week 9
[size=18][i][b]Welcome to the SRF![/b][/size]
We pride ourselves on a friendly, competitive and yet relaxed atmosphere both on and off-track. Don't be afraid to ask for help, either in practice sessions or on the forum![/i]

[img]https://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/downloadAttach/2542173.page[/img]

[color=red][size=18]Spec Racer Ford Challenge Series @ [b] Suzuka International Course - West[/b]
Week 9 of 12 - 2019 Season 3 [/size][/color]
Race Distance: [b]20 laps[/b], approximately 25 minutes
World Record lap time: [b]1:31.269[/b] by Aday Coba Lopez (Qualifying)
(n.b. random/dynamic weather impacts lap times greatly)

Welcome to the world-famous Suzuka International Circuit - home to some fantastic Grand Prix racing over many years. This track makes for some great SRF racing, so it's definitely worth the effort to learn it! This time we are using the West layout, which comprises most of the second half of the GP layout. From the Degner Curves through the Hairpin to Spoon and 130R, these are some iconic and challenging corners!

Typically the best SoF races are usually the first race of the week, and 22:45 GMT Sunday (following the Weekend Warriors league race)

[img]https://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/downloadAttach/2542174.page[/img]

